{"TopicId":190444,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"[KSPAddon(Startup","CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-18T03:24:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-18T03:24:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need a mod to work in both Flight and Tracking Station, but the KSPAddon\u00A0attribute\u0027s startup parameter cannot be bitwise or\u0027d and the attribute cannot have multiple declarations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nany ideas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Benjamin Kerman","CreatedById":172792,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-18T03:26:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can have it start in all scenes and then either do nothing or terminate if the current scene isn\u0027t Flight or Tracking Station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: that\u0027s HighLogic.fetch.LoadedScene\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-18T03:30:03Z\u0022 title=\u002212/18/2019 03:30  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 18, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Benjamin Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-18T03:42:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably the least worst pattern I\u0027ve seen is to derive multiple scene-specific shell classes from your main MonoBehaviour class and then tag each one with the appropriate attribute. E.g., that\u0027s what \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E does:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/TriggerAu/KerbalAlarmClock/blob/c5f813cd8a4e7a4ea5afc74b65f74a702188fbfb/KerbalAlarmClock/KerbalAlarmClock.cs#L31-L55\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/TriggerAu/KerbalAlarmClock/blob/c5f813cd8a4e7a4ea5afc74b65f74a702188fbfb/KerbalAlarmClock/KerbalAlarmClock.cs#L31-L55\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot ideal, but it gets the job done without too much fuss.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-18T03:43:14Z\u0022 title=\u002212/18/2019 03:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 18, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by HebaruSan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xyphos","CreatedById":139010,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-18T03:55:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223718533\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221576640567\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably the least worst pattern I\u0027ve seen is to derive multiple scene-specific shell classes from your main MonoBehaviour class and then tag each one with the appropriate attribute. E.g., that\u0027s what \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Engineer Redux (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E does:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/TriggerAu/KerbalAlarmClock/blob/c5f813cd8a4e7a4ea5afc74b65f74a702188fbfb/KerbalAlarmClock/KerbalAlarmClock.cs#L31-L55\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/TriggerAu/KerbalAlarmClock/blob/c5f813cd8a4e7a4ea5afc74b65f74a702188fbfb/KerbalAlarmClock/KerbalAlarmClock.cs#L31-L55\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot ideal, but it gets the job done without too much fuss.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI considered doing it that way, but I was worried if Unity wouldn\u0027t fire the inherited methods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"micha","CreatedById":113840,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-18T05:54:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223718535\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221576641359\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139010\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xyphos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Xyphos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI considered doing it that way, but I was worried if Unity wouldn\u0027t fire the inherited methods.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDebug.Log to the rescue if you can\u0027t use a debugger.\u00A0 Try it out and see what happens (then document it for the rest of us \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E ).\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}